Customer relationship management (CRM) functionality helps companies manage their interaction with current and potential customers to identify and address effectively their target audience’s needs and build a strong relationship with the customers.{br}
Acumatica ERP provides tools for process automation, data management, and reporting for marketing, sales and customer support teams.{br}
You can easily customize the CRM functionality to fit your company’s business goals, streamline your marketing, sales, and customer support processes, and ensure higher profitability.[anchor|#_b5bb63b6-03fe-4ca6-8e34-9931cffd5e61] ==Overview of Marketing Processes== Marketing functionality in Acumatica ERP helps marketing teams acquire, manage, and qualify leads, handle marketing lists and marketing subscriptions, manage marketing campaigns, and generate marketing reports.{br}
Processing leads by marketing personnel may consist of the following stages:[anchor|#_ac17a1e0-8db0-4763-97be-732f59445c1d] *Creating leads. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Creating_Leads_Mapref|Creating Leads]. *Validating leads for duplicates. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Validating_Recs_Duplicates_Mapref|Validating Records for Duplicates]. *Assigning leads to owners. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Assigning_Leads_To_Owners_Mapref|Assigning Leads To Owners]. *Managing leads. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Managing_Emails_Activities_Mapref|Managing Emails and Activities]. *Managing marketing lists. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Mng_Marketing_Lists_Mapref|Managing Marketing Lists]. *Managing marketing campaigns. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Mng_Marketing_Campaigns_Mapref|Managing Marketing Campaigns]. *Qualifying leads. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Qualifying_Leads_by_Marketing_Mapref|Qualifying Leads (Marketing)]. *Analyzing marketing results and performance of a marketing team by generating reports. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__MNG_Reports|Managing CRM Reports]. [anchor|#_aa3f5b63-a379-428f-a866-bb6c6d72862b] ==Overview of Sales Processes== Sales functionality in Acumatica ERP helps sales teams manage and qualify leads, create contacts and business accounts for prospects, create, manage and advance opportunities through stages, manage opportunity-based quotes, sales orders, and invoices, and generate sales reports.{br}
Processing leads and customers by sales personnel may consist of the following stages:[anchor|#_90fe1efc-c848-40fa-a185-b411b14a692e] *Assigning leads to owners. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Assigning_Leads_To_Owners_Mapref|Assigning Leads To Owners]. *Managing leads. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Managing_Emails_Activities_Mapref|Managing Emails and Activities]. *Validating contacts and accounts for duplicates. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Validating_Recs_Duplicates_Mapref|Validating Records for Duplicates]. *Creating contacts. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Sales_Creating_Contacts_Mapref|Creating Contacts]. *Creating business accounts. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Sales_Creating_Bus_Accounts_Mapref|Creating Business Accounts]. *Managing opportunities. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__MNG_Opportunities|Managing Opportunities]. *Analyzing sales results and performance of a sales team by generating reports. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__MNG_Reports|Managing CRM Reports].
==Overview of Customer Support Processes== Customer support functionality in Acumatica ERP gives you the ability to track support cases (tickets) through to resolution. The communication with your customer can begin when a customer creates a new case on the Acumatica Self-Service Portal, sends an email, or makes a phone call to your customer support service.{br}
Service and support activities are integrated with other functional area in Acumatica ERP —such as sales, marketing, field services, and financials—to deliver a team-oriented approach to customer support and increased sales. You can automate escalations as assignment of cases that come in to your organization.{br}
Processing cases by customer support personnel may consist of the following stages:[anchor|#_0c4db1d6-115c-40d1-8089-4771f95b1dcd] *Creating support cases. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__MNG_Cases|Managing Cases]. *Assigning cases to owners. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__con_Case_Assignment|Case Assignment]. *Processing cases. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__con_Case_Processing|Case Processing]. *Creating a service order for the service dispatcher. For details, see [HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__MNG_Processing_Service_Orders|Processing Service Orders]. *Creating and appointment for the service technician. For details, see [HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__MNG_Processing_Appointments|Processing Appointments]. *Releasing cases ans creating the associated invoices. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__con_Case_Billing|Case Billing]. *Analyzing results and performance of customer. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CR__MNG_Reports|Managing CRM Reports].

