==Applicable Scenarios== You may want to learn how to register leads in Acumatica ERP in scenarios that include the following:[anchor|#_b05069d0-39f8-413d-828b-293a72e39344] *You have obtained some contact information about a potential customer. *You have acquired a list of cold leads (individuals or organizations who never contacted your organization or expressed any interest in your products or services) from a vendor or a public source. *You have started working with the system and need to import your existing leads from your legacy system into Acumatica ERP. *You have received an email from a potential customer.
==Marketing Leads in Acumatica ERP== A marketing lead is contact information representing a person or a company that has a potential interest in products or services your organization offers. Leads make up the organization’s marketing audience, which is the target for marketing activities, such as marketing campaigns or advertisements.{br}
A marketing manager defines the organization’s marketing strategy, goals, and target audience, as well as acquiring and managing data on the marketing audience. When the audience data has been acquired, the marketing manager can create the needed leads in the system. ==Lead Creation== Lead creation in Acumatica ERP consists of either or both of the following general steps:[anchor|#_f71404f5-e328-44c1-8aa4-0dd911a12e61] *Creating leads manually *Importing lead data from external sources
As soon as leads have been added to the system and checked for duplicates, as described in [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Validating_Recs_Duplicates_Mapref|Validating Records for Duplicates], you can assign these leads to owners either one by one or in batches according to the rules that have been specified in the system, and the owners start working on these leads, as described in [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Assigning_Leads_To_Owners_Mapref|Assigning Leads To Owners].{br}
In Acumatica ERP, you can create a lead in any of the following ways:[anchor|#_c147d045-4dee-4191-9dc8-4ff1a92b6ce6] *By manually entering lead data on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form. For detailed instructions, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Creating_Leads_Create_Lead|Creating Leads: To Create a Lead Manually]. *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) or [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]) form, if you click '''Actions''' > '''Create Lead'''. *By using import scenarios to import lists of leads on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_60_36|Import by Scenario] ([~/?ScreenId=SM206036|SM206036]) form. For detailed instructions, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Creating_Leads_Import_List_of_Leads|Creating Leads: To Import Leads From a Purchased List]. *By creating a lead from the Acumatica add-in for Outlook based on the details of the selected email recipient or sender. For detailed instructions, see [HelpRoot_Integration\OU_00_00_00| Acumatica Add-In for Outlook] and [HelpRoot_Integration\OU__how_To_Create_Lead|To Create a Lead by Using the Acumatica Add-In]. *By enabling integration with web services on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_70_40|Web Services] ([~/?ScreenId=SM207040|SM207040]) form for the automatic import of leads. For details, see [HelpRoot_Dev_Customization\CG_GL_Items_WebServices|Web Service Endpoints]. *By using the integration with HubSpot. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\config_HubSpot_Mapref|Configuring Integration with HubSpot]. *By activating the functionality of incoming mail processing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_40_02|System Email Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=SM204002|SM204002]) form for the automatic creation of leads based on information about the sender. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\EM__con_Mail_Processing|Incoming Mail Processing].
==Contact Information== On the '''Contact Info''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form, you can specify the name, contact information, and address of the selected lead. Also, this tab holds information about the lead's consent to the processing of personal data if the ''GDPR Compliance Tools'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. (For details about GDPR compliance tools, see [HelpRoot_Administration\GD__MNG_Handling_Personal_Data|Handling Personal Data].){br}
If the '''Override''' check box on the '''Contact Info''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] form is cleared, the contact information of the selected lead is synchronized with the contact information of the related contact and business account on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) form and the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]) form, respectively. If the check box is selected, the contact information for the selected lead on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] form can differ from the contact information of the related record on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] and [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] forms, as well as from the contact information of the leads related to this lead. The synchronization or overriding of settings applies to all the settings on the '''Contact Info''' tab.[anchor|#_c1c19014-a7b4-4630-87e6-56caaa0420d7] ==Synchronization of Settings in Leads, Contacts, and Business Accounts== In Acumatica ERP, you can easily synchronize the contact-related settings of a lead with the same settings in the contact and business account related to that lead. With this synchronization turned on, changes to the contact information of any of these entities causes the settings in the related entities to be updated as well.((({S:Hint}The synchronization or overriding of settings applies to all the settings on the '''Contact Info''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form, all the settings on the '''Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) form, and the contact and address settings (of the primary contact of the business account) on the '''General''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]) form. ))) You can synchronize contact information in leads, contacts, and business accounts by using the '''Override''' check box on the '''Contact Info''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) form as follows:[anchor|#_a0399093-c279-47e6-bd3d-d4ef6beb89d7] *If the check box is cleared and the business account related to the contact has not been converted to a customer or a vendor yet, the contact information of the contact on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] form is synchronized with the contact information of the related lead and business account on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] and [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] forms, respectively, and can be updated in both directions. That is, if you update the contact and address settings on any of these forms, the settings will be also updated on the related forms. *If the check box is selected, the contact information for the selected contact on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] form can differ from the contact information of the related lead and business account on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] and [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] forms. If contact information is updated on any of these forms, the changes are not related on the other forms.
==Flexible Classification of Leads== In Acumatica ERP, you can easily categorize leads into different classes and gather different sets of additional information about leads of different classes. When you create a new lead, the system can automatically assign a class to this lead and you can change the class as needed. For each class, you can create a set of attributes, which give users the ability to further classify leads within the class. For each attribute, you can define the type of control that represents it in the UI (check box, text box, or combo box) and specify the possible values, if applicable. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Classes_Mapref|Configuring Classes in CRM].{br}
When a class for a lead has been selected, the attributes assigned to this class appear on the '''Attributes''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form as additional elements that can be used to specify information about a lead.{br}
An administrator can customize the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form to add to the Summary area the '''User-Defined Fields''' tab that holds the attributes. By using these fields, you can easily specify the attributes for the leads you are working with.

Duplicate records in your marketing data may cause data quality problems that result in lost productivity for your marketing and sales teams. A large number of duplicate leads, contacts, and business accounts could trigger the sending of the same marketing materials multiple times to the same contact or business account. The probability of duplicates significantly increases each time that you add to the system a large batch of new records.{br}
To address these issues, Acumatica ERP provides flexible tools for eliminating duplicate records.{br}{TOC} ==Learning Objectives== In this chapter, you will learn how to do the following:[anchor|#_8a8af48d-35e1-4324-a417-9af050c177af] *Validate leads and contacts for duplicates *Merge duplicate leads *Link leads and contacts
==Applicable Scenarios== You may want to learn how to validate records for duplicates in Acumatica ERP in either (or both) of the following cases:[anchor|#_e509b2a7-3c13-414d-9d66-34baf9be23eb] *You have imported to the system a batch of new leads and need to check these leads for duplicates. *You regularly validate all records in the system for duplicates, and it is time to again initiate this process. [anchor|#_b367349b-5a4a-475c-9fd0-1c05a60f750b] ==Duplicate Validation in Acumatica ERP== When a new lead, contact, or business account is created in the system, Acumatica ERP can check the newly created record for duplicates on entry (when the record is saved for the first time) or at the request of the user.{br}
Records can be validated for duplicates if the following setup tasks have been performed in the system:[anchor|#_e21bc387-cf6a-49a4-b93e-5dccc3e7f55d] #The ''Lead/Contact Duplicate Validation'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. #Default duplicate validation rules have been defined for each type of records (leads, contacts, and business accounts) on the '''Duplicate Validation Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_10_10_00|Customer Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=CR101000|CR101000]) form. For more details, see [[#_924721b8-4821-4871-961c-fd6e58697cdf|Duplicate Validation Rules for Leads, Contacts, and Business Accounts]. #Additional duplicate validation settings should also be specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_10_10_00|Customer Management Preferences] form. For more details, see [[#_2ba2065e-ca10-4d52-9a37-c9c9392a7943|Additional Duplicate Validation Settings]. #The calculation of grams, which are used for the calculation of validation scores, has been performed for each contact, lead, or business account record on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_34_00|Calculate Grams] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503400|CR503400]) form. For more details, see [[#_0954a1df-8f02-48a9-be29-c28a296e7eb3|Calculation of Validation Scores].
After the setup tasks have been performed, users can validate records for duplicates, as described in [[#_6e44cf9f-926b-48e8-b71d-932190e18d25|Validation of Records for Duplicates]. They can merge duplicate records into one record, which involves updating the information in the target record and closing the duplicate record. (For details, see [[#_e5c77f3d-093b-4eb4-bc9d-4ff252988c54|Merging of Records on the Duplicates Tab].) Optionally, users can link the related leads, contacts, and business accounts, as described in [[#_c44677c4-a874-4691-9ca2-446047a2f853|Linking of Records on the Duplicates Tab]. As a result, the leads, contacts, and business accounts in the system are free of duplication, which improves productivity for the personnel, who can now work with consistent and reliable data.[anchor|#_924721b8-4821-4871-961c-fd6e58697cdf] ==Duplicate Validation Rules for Leads, Contacts, and Business Accounts== Lead, contact, and business account records have the same internal fields (and corresponding UI elements), which contain the contact and address settings of a person or company. By using the settings on the '''Duplicate Validation Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_10_10_00|Customer Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=CR101000|CR101000]) form, you can specify your organization’s rules for duplicate validation. You can select the fields according to your criteria; for example, you can compare only email addresses or compare multiple settings, such as email addresses, last names, and company names.{br}
You determine how the duplicate validation process is performed by using the '''Duplicate Validation Settings''' tab. The lower part of this tab contains three tabs, where you specify various duplication validation rules. During the duplication validation process, the system does the following:[anchor|#_59d6bd33-b12e-4bb1-b753-330c8e6b0d5a] *Validates leads against other leads, contacts, and business accounts according to the rules specified on the '''Lead and Contact Validation Rules''' tab. *Validates contacts against other contacts and leads based on the rules specified on the '''Lead and Contact Validation Rules''' tab. *Validates leads against business accounts using the rules specified on the '''Lead and Account Validation Rules''' tab. *Validates business accounts against other business accounts based on the rules specified on the '''Account Validation Rules''' tab.
Consider the example of the lead and contact validation rules shown in the following screenshot.[anchor|#_3fea5f10-e084-434b-9ae6-047c1400baa4][anchor|#_826d8cd2-3d1b-44cf-a68c-fd17bcf1a8f4][image:UserGuide/Images/CRM_Duplicate_Validation_GeneralInfo_Lead_Contact_Valid_Rules_1.png|popup|Example of duplicate validation rules for leads and contacts |750px] You can use the following elements on the tab (which correspond to the items labeled in the screenshot):[anchor|#_02645c42-f746-44db-8221-5a09a8c99719] #'''Lead and Contact Validation Rules''' tab: Here you can specify settings (matching fields, score weights, and transformation rules) for lead and contact validation. #'''Matching Field''' column: In this column, you can specify each field whose values the system will compare during the validation process. #'''Score Weight''' column: The score weight you specify here indicates the share that the field contributes to the total validation score if two values match. The total validation score of a pair of compared records is calculated as the sum of the weights of the fields whose values match. By using the rules specified in the example shown in the screenshot, if email addresses match, the weight of 1.5 is added, and if both email addresses and last names match, the weight of 3.5 is added. #'''Transformation Rule''' column: For each listed field, this column contains one of the following options, which indicate the rule the system will use to transform the matching field values before comparing them: #*''None'': No additional rules are applied; the whole values are compared as they are. #*''Split Words'': The system will compare separate words that make up the two values. #*''Domain Name'': The system will compare the applicable domain name, such as ''domain.com''. In an email address or a URL (the ''Web'' field), the system will use the domain part of the address. For example, if the email address is ''email@example.com'', then only ''example.com'' will be used for comparison. #'''Lead and Contact Validation Threshold''' box (Summary area of the tab): Here you can specify the threshold value used to determine whether the compared records are possible duplicates. #:((({S:Hint}The total score of the fields listed in the '''Score Weight''' column should be greater than or the same as the value in the '''Lead and Contact Validation Threshold''' box. )))
With the settings shown in the screenshot above, during lead and contact duplicate validation, the system compares all the values in the '''Score Weight''' column, adds the validation scores for the values that match, and then compares the total validation score against the threshold specified in the '''Lead and Contact Validation Threshold''' box. If the total validation score equals or exceeds this threshold value, the compared records are considered possible duplicates.[anchor|#_2ba2065e-ca10-4d52-9a37-c9c9392a7943] ==Additional Duplicate Validation Settings== On the '''Duplicate Validation Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_10_10_00|Customer Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=CR101000|CR101000]) form, you can specify additional duplicate validation settings to do the following:[anchor|#_74671cd7-553a-4812-9942-a034fdb52697] *Validate a lead or contact for duplicates on entry: If you select the '''Validate Leads and Contacts for Duplicates on Entry''' check box, the system will validate each new lead or contact as soon as a user creates the record on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) or [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) form and saves the record for the first time. As a result of validation, the record is given the duplicate status of either ''Validated'' or ''Possible Duplicate'': The system inserts one of these values in the '''Duplicate''' box of the Summary area. *Validate a business account for duplicates on entry: If you select the '''Validate Accounts for Duplicates on Entry''' check box, the system will validate each new business account as soon as a user creates the account on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]) form and saves the record for the first time. As a result of validation, the business account is given the duplicate status of either ''Validated'' or ''Possible Duplicate'': The system inserts one of these values in the '''Duplicate''' box of the Summary area. *Validate a lead or contact for duplicates base on the email address of the lead or contact: If you select the '''Require Unique Email Address on Contact Validation''' check box, the system will validate each new lead or contact email address for duplication as soon as a user specifies the email address on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] or [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] form and saves the record for the first time. As a result of validation, the record is given the duplicate status of either ''Validated'' or ''Possible Duplicate'': The system inserts one of these values in the '''Duplicate''' box of the Summary area. [anchor|#_0954a1df-8f02-48a9-be29-c28a296e7eb3] ==Calculation of Validation Scores== In Acumatica ERP, grams are used for the calculation of validation scores for each lead, contact, or business account. Each record has a number of settings, such as {{Last Name}}, {{Email}}, or {{Class ID}}. The grams value assigned to a particular record is defined by the total number of settings that are involved in the calculation of the validation score.{br}
As a rule, validation scores are calculated automatically if the ''Lead/Contact Duplicate Validation'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form.{br}
You need to recalculate validation scores on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_34_00|Calculate Grams] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503400|CR503400]) form in the following cases:((({S:Warn}The [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_34_00|Calculate Grams] form is available only if the ''Lead/Contact Duplicate Validation'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. )))[anchor|#_48ce7f5c-95b6-48e6-8d78-e29336b4289c] *Validation rules have been changed on the '''Duplicate Validation Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_10_10_00|Customer Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=CR101000|CR101000]) form. *The ''Lead/Contact Duplicate Validation'' feature was temporarily disabled while a batch of new records was imported into Acumatica ERP and then was enabled again. [anchor|#_6e44cf9f-926b-48e8-b71d-932190e18d25] ==Validation of Records for Duplicates== Acumatica ERP provides the ability to mass-validate groups of records for duplicates and to validate individual records.{br}
To mass-validate records, you can use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_34_10|Validate Leads and Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503410|CR503410]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_34_20|Validate Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503420|CR503420]) forms. On these forms, you can validate either records with the ''Not Validated'' duplicate status or all listed records.((({S:Warn}Validating all the records in the system may be a time-consuming process if you are validating a very large number of records. You can speed up duplicate validation by using parallel processing. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Validating_Recs_Duplicates_Mapref|Validating Records for Duplicates]. ))){br}
If you validate all records, once you click '''Process All''' on the form toolbar, the system starts processing records one by one, first changing the duplicate status of each record to ''Not Validated'' in the '''Duplicate''' box of the Summary area on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form for a lead and the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) form for each contact. As a result of validation, each record is given a duplicate status of either ''Validated'' or ''Possible Duplicate''.((({S:Warn}We recommend that you not interrupt the duplicate validation process. If you do, you will not be able to resume it; each time you click '''Process All''', the processing starts anew for all listed records. ))){br}
You can validate individual records by manually executing the '''Check for Duplicates''' action, which is available in the '''Actions''' menu on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads], [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts], and [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]) data entry forms, as described in [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Validating_Recs_Duplicates_Validate_Multiple_Leads|Validating Records for Duplicates: To Validate Multiple Leads for Duplicates]. Also, new records can be validated on entry if the corresponding settings have been specified on the '''Duplicate Validation Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_10_10_00|Customer Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=CR101000|CR101000]) form. In this case, validation scores are calculated for each new record on entry so that you do not have to manually run the gram recalculation process on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_34_00|Calculate Grams] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503400|CR503400]) form.{br}
If at least one possible duplicate has been found for a record, the '''Duplicates''' tab appears on the corresponding data entry form: [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads], [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts], or [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts]. On this tab, you can merge duplicate records into one record or link records, as described in the following sections.[anchor|#_e5c77f3d-093b-4eb4-bc9d-4ff252988c54] ==Merging of Records on the Duplicates Tab== When you have performed validation for duplicates (whether validation has been performed for a group of records or an individual record), you can merge duplicate records relative to the lead, contact, or business account selected on the data entry form on the '''Duplicates''' tab of the respective form as follows:[anchor|#_a5aa1760-d9a8-4215-8bc3-e487ffb4e98c] *On this tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form, you can merge the target lead you select with the selected duplicate lead. Before merging leads, you should indicate to the system which settings to use: those of the target lead or those of the duplicate lead. *On this tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) form, you can merge the target contact you select with the selected duplicate contact. Before merging contacts, you should indicate to the system which settings to use: those of the target contact or those of the duplicate contact. *On this tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]) form, you can merge the target business account you select with the selected duplicate business account. Before merging business accounts, you should indicate to the system which settings to use: those of the target business account or those of the duplicate account. ((({S:Danger}The system does not allow merging of leads that are associated with different contacts: You cannot select such leads for merging. ))) When you have resolved conflicts between the matching fields and merged the target record with the duplicate record, the duplicate record is no longer displayed on the '''Duplicates''' tab. For the duplicate record, the system inserts the ''Duplicated'' value in the ''' Duplicate''' box of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads], [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts], or [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] form (Summary area) and closes this record as duplicate. Also, most of the settings in the Summary area of the form and the settings on the tabs of the form become unavailable for editing. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Validating_Recs_Duplicates_Validating_Lead|Validating Records for Duplicates: To Validate a Lead for Duplicates].[anchor|#_c44677c4-a874-4691-9ca2-446047a2f853] ==Linking of Records on the Duplicates Tab== When you have performed validation for duplicates (whether validation has been performed for a group of records or an individual record), you can associate leads with contacts or business accounts, or contacts with leads and business accounts on the '''Duplicates''' tab of the respective form as follows:[anchor|#_aa811ecb-2604-471a-a365-d71b702b54da] *On this tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form, you can associate the lead selected on the form with a contact or business account. When you associate the lead with a contact or business account by clicking '''Link to Entity''' on the table toolbar of the '''Duplicates''' tab, you can see the contact or business account in the '''Contact''' or '''Account''' box in the Summary area of the form. Before associating the selected lead with a contact or business account, you should indicate to the system which settings to use: those of the target lead or those of the contact or business account with which you are associating with the lead. *On this tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) form, you can associate the contact selected on the form with a lead or business account. When you associate the contact with a lead or business account by clicking '''Link to Entity''', you can see the lead on the '''Leads''' tab of the form or the business account in the '''Account''' box in the Summary area of the form. Before associating the selected contact with a lead or business account, you should indicate to the system which settings to use: those of the target contact or those of the lead or business account with which you are associating with the contact.
When you have associated a record with the lead, contact, or business account, this record is no longer displayed on the '''Duplicates''' tab. For details, see [HelpRoot_CRM\CRM_Mktg_Validating_Recs_Duplicates_Validating_Lead|Validating Records for Duplicates: To Validate a Lead for Duplicates].

Acumatica ERP provides you with flexible tools for distributing the workload among responsible persons in the company. You can use assignment maps to indicate to the system how to assign records—such as leads, opportunities, or cases—to persons or groups of persons. This topic provides information about assigning leads to owners one by one or through mass processing.{br}{TOC} ==Learning Objectives== In this chapter, you will learn how to do the following:[anchor|#ul_dmx_2lv_pr] *Assign a lead manually to a particular owner *In a lead class, specify how the system determines the default owner it specifies for new leads of the class *Assign a selected group of leads to owners by using a lead assignment map
==Applicable Scenarios== You may want to learn how to assign leads to owners in scenarios that include the following:[anchor|#_7165d0ed-fbf9-4bca-b563-a0155c7a9310] *You have acquired a new lead and need to assign this lead to a particular person or a group of persons for nurturing. *You have been requested to work with a lead and need to specify yourself as an owner. *You have imported to the system a new batch of leads, such as a purchased list, and need to distribute these leads among the employees of the applicable department or group, such as a marketing department.
==Distribution of Leads Between Owners in Acumatica ERP== In Acumatica ERP, you can easily base the rules for lead assignment on company policies because leads can be distributed among owners (individuals) or workgroups (groups of people) in many different ways, based on the settings and attributes of the lead records being distributed. You can distribute leads manually or automatically. You can manually assign leads individually or in groups. When you create a lead on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form or at any later time, you can select an owner in the '''Owner''' box of the Summary area. You can also manually change the owner of a lead that has been manually or automatically assigned. You can assign groups of leads that do not have owners specified by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_30_10|Assign Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503010|CR503010]) mass processing form. On this form, you can assign selected leads or all leads that do not have owners, and the system uses the assignment map specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_10_10_00|Customer Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=CR101000|CR101000]) form to determine the owners of the leads.{br}
You can cause leads to be automatically assigned to owners by specifying a setting for any lead class that determines how the default owner is assigned to new leads of the class. On the '''Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_70_00|Lead Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR207000|CR207000]) form for a lead class, based on the option you select in the '''Default Owner''' box, the system assigns one of the following as the default owner of a new lead of the class:[anchor|#_5513b980-d051-429a-bcad-f4bd0e0bfdba] *The user that created the lead (''Creator'' option) *A user determined by the assignment map you specify (''Assignment Map'' option) *The owner specified for the contact or business account from which the lead was created (''From source entity'' option), if you created the lead in this way {br}
If you want the system to distribute leads by using an assignment map, whether to assign the owner of leads of a particular class or to be used for mass-assignment of leads, you must perform two preliminary tasks. You can first create a company tree on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_40_61|Company Tree] ([~/?ScreenId=EP204061|EP204061]) form, as described in the following section. Then you can create the needed maps for the automatic assignment of leads by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_50_10|Assignment Maps] ([~/?ScreenId=EP205010|EP205010]) form.[anchor|#_f86d138a-4d4f-4eee-b2f3-2d13e51b348f] ==The Company Tree and Workgroups== Maintaining and using a functional organizational chart in an ERP system can facilitate the assignment of work and approvals for optimal collaboration within teams and smoother workflows. In Acumatica ERP, a company tree is a hierarchical structure that contains groups of persons, roles of persons, and chains of assignments and approvals. A company tree may include both an organizational chart of a company with different levels of management and a hierarchy of groups representing real business relations and functions.{br}
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_40_61|Company Tree] ([~/?ScreenId=EP204061|EP204061]) form, you can easily create various hierarchies of groups for approvals or assignments, and include the same persons or groups of persons in different workgroups. Thus, users can participate in multiple workflows. You can use approvals for cross-department projects, which have a manager and project participants that may belong to different company departments but be members of the same chain of approvals. We recommend using a company tree to speed and streamline your assignments and approvals. ==Distribution of Leads by Using Lead Classes== As noted previously, when you create or modify a lead class on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_70_00|Lead Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR207000|CR207000]) form, you can specify how the system automatically assigns the owner to newly created leads of the class. You do this by selecting the appropriate option in the '''Default Owner''' box on the '''Details''' tab ('''Data Entry Settings''' section). Based on the selected option selected for the lead class, when a lead class has been selected for a lead on the '''CRM Info''' tab ('''CRM''' section) of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form, the system determines the default owner of this lead and inserts the appropriate employee name in the '''Owner''' box in the Summary area of the form.{br}
In the '''Default Owner''' box of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_70_00|Lead Classes] form, you select one of the following options for the lead class:[anchor|#_62415367-6863-4b3f-bdc2-937212d338d9] *''Creator'': When a lead of the class is created, the user who created the lead record is assigned as its owner by default. *''Assignment Map'': When a lead of the class is created, based on the assignment map (which you must also select in the '''Assignment Map''' box for the class), the system determines the default owner or workgroup (or both) and inserts them on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] form. The system inserts the workgroup of the lead, if applicable, on the '''CRM Info''' tab ('''CRM''' section). If you are distributing leads based on assignment maps, you can use a different assignment map for each lead class, if needed. *''From Source Entity'': When a lead of the class is created, if it is created from another entity, such as a contact, or business account, the lead inherits the owner and workgroup (if specified) from this contact or business account. This default owner is assigned if you create a lead from a contact on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) form or from a business account on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]) form.
We recommend distributing leads by using lead classes because the system assigns a lead to an owner each time a new lead record is created. ==Distribution of Leads by Using Assignment Maps== You can use the assignment map functionality to distribute leads automatically through the use of lead classes or manually when you mass-assign leads.[anchor|#_8681a850-8b58-4781-9eda-61e9dbae8c41]{br}
An assignment map is a set of steps, rules, and conditions that can be used for assigning a record or a number of records for processing to a particular person or a group of persons. An assignment map may include any number of rules, which are executed sequentially. Each rule in an assignment map includes conditions and actions to be performed if the conditions are met. You create assignment maps on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_50_10|Assignment Maps] ([~/?ScreenId=EP205010|EP205010]) form as follows: [anchor|#_9fd6b996-08b9-4cc7-9d4d-d794838bf0d6] *On the '''Rules''' tree, you add new rules. *On the '''Conditions''' tab, you add conditions that assignment criteria should meet. *On the '''Rule Actions''' tab, you select an owner or a workgroup (or both). {br}
Once a lead assignment map has been created, you can do any of the following:[anchor|#_b5efe1fd-82ff-488a-8a90-90db6f49e719] *Specify the assignment map on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_70_00|Lead Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR207000|CR207000]) form for the lead class if you have selected ''Assignment Map'' in the '''Default Owner''' box on the '''Details''' tab: Each new lead of the class will be assigned to a default owner according to this map. A user can change the owner as needed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form. *Specify the assignment map on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_10_10_00|Customer Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=CR101000|CR101000]) form, in the '''Lead Assignment Map''' box of the '''General Settings''' tab ('''Assignment Settings '''section): Existing leads that do not have owners will be assigned to owners according to this map if you assign the leads by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_30_10|Assign Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503010|CR503010]) mass processing form. ((({S:Warn}The assignment map specified for the applicable lead class on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_70_00|Lead Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR207000|CR207000]) form overrides the assignment map specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_10_10_00|Customer Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=CR101000|CR101000]) form. Leads of the class will be assigned to owners according to the assignment map from the lead class. ))) ==Execution Issues Related to a Lead Assignment Map== If an assignment map contains errors (for example, a workgroup contains an employee who has quit the company and cannot be assigned to any records), and you have processed any leads that should be assigned according to this assignment map by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_50_30_10|Assign Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR503010|CR503010]) form, the system will list these errors in the '''Processing''' dialog box. You can view the error by clicking the More button on the '''Errors''' tile in this dialog box. In the '''Message''' column, the system displays the text of the error message. ==Notifications About Assigning a Lead to an Owner== In Acumatica ERP, an administrator can set up email notifications on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_30_20_50|Business Events] ([~/?ScreenId=SM302050|SM302050]) form so that if you are assigned to a new lead, you receive a notification by email, by SMS, or in Acumatica mobile app. For details, see [HelpRoot_Dev_Customization\CG_GL_Items_BusinessEvents|Business Events].

The following activity demonstrates how to assign leads to owners and set up the system to assign leads to owners automatically. The activity will show you how to define a lead class so that leads of the class are assigned to their creators by default. You will also practice manually assigning leads to the appropriate owners, both for an individual lead and by using the mass-processing form to assign multiple users to the needed owners.[anchor|#_68a3c30c-a10c-460d-a5ec-160718c20d93]((({S:Danger}The following activity is based on the ''U100'' dataset. If you are using another dataset, or if any system settings have been changed in ''U100'', these changes can affect the workflow of the activity and the results of the processing. To avoid any issues, restore the ''U100'' dataset to its initial state. ))) ==Story== Suppose that you are Bill Owen, a new marketing manager of the SweetLife Fruits & Jams company, and you are performing several tasks related to assigning leads to the appropriate owner. First, you need to modify an existing lead class (the class for confectioneries) so that by default, when a new lead of the class is created, the system assigns the lead’s creator as its owner. Also, a new lead, ''Stanley Carson'', has been created in the system, and you want to manually assign this lead to you and to your workgroup. {br}
A number of leads whose companies can be classified as stores (including supermarkets) and food service companies (bakeries, cafes, or restaurants) have been imported into the system, and you want to distribute these leads between two workgroups of marketing employees as follows:[anchor|#_e0798017-41d6-4a7e-a20c-38f0f505480f] *The ''Marketing Stores'' workgroup will be working with leads that represent supermarkets and other stores. *The ''Marketing Food Services'' workgroup, to which your ''owen'' user account belongs, will be working with leads that represent restaurants, cafes, bakeries, and other food service companies.
The needed workgroups have been defined in the company tree and an assignment map has been created to assign leads to the needed workgroup; also, you have specified the needed configuration setting to cause the system to use this assignment map when you are mass-assigning leads. You will mass-assign leads by using this assignment map. ==Configuration Overview== In the ''U100'' dataset, for the purposes of this activity, the following tasks have been performed:[anchor|#_98489720-14ad-46d0-aed9-fc4ec675c7fc] *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form, the ''Customer Management'' feature has been enabled. This feature provides the customer relationship management (CRM) functionality, including lead and customer tracking, as well as the handling of sales opportunities, contacts, marketing lists, and campaigns. *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_40_61|Company Tree] ([~/?ScreenId=EP204061|EP204061]) form, the company tree has been configured and it includes the ''Marketing Supermarkets'' and the ''Marketing Food Services'' workgroups as well as the users in the Marketing department. *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_50_10|Assignment Maps] ([~/?ScreenId=EP205010|EP205010]) form, the ''Lead Assignment Map'' has been created. According to the rule actions specified in the assignment map, the leads of the ''STORE'' class are assigned to the ''Marketing Supermarkets'' workgroup in the SweetLife marketing department, and the leads of the ''BAKERY'' and ''CAFE'' classes are assigned to the ''Marketing Food Services'' workgroup in the marketing department. *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_10_10_00|Customer Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=CR101000|CR101000]) form (in the '''Lead Assignment Map''' box of the '''Assignment Settings''' section of the '''General Settings''' tab), the lead assignment map has been specified. The system will use this assignment map during the process of mass-assigning leads. *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_20_70_00|Lead Classes] ([~/?ScreenId=CR207000|CR207000]) form, the following lead classes have been created: ''STORE'' (for leads that are supermarkets and other stores), ''BAKERY'', ''CAFE'' (which includes leads that are restaurants and cafes), and ''SWEETSHOP'' (for leads that are confectioneries). *A list of lead records that includes bakeries, cafes, restaurants, and supermarkets has been imported to the system through the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_60_36|Import by Scenario] ([~/?ScreenId=SM206036|SM206036]) form. *On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) form, the following leads—which have been assigned to, respectively, the ''STORE'', ''BAKERY'', and ''CAFE'' lead classes—have been added to the system: ''Stanley Carson'', ''Douglas Keatinge'', and ''Duncan Saunders''.
